Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Feb (MENA)--The Sudanese opposition 
al-Ummah Party issued a statement in Cairo today holding the 
Sudanese Government fully responsible for opening the country's 
territory to terrorists and noting, in this connection, the 
Sudanese Foreign Ministry's decision to grant citizenship to 
members of all Islamic groups. 
  The party announced that the Sudanese Government is 
responsible for last Saturday's assault against the residence 
and company headquarters of a Saudi businessman living in Sudan. 
Several security personnel were injured in that incident. 
  The statement warned the Sudanese Government of the 
consequences of playing patron to terrorists. 

